  codename: "Maximum Caliber — Principle of Maximum Caliber for Path Entropy"

summary: |
  Introduces the Principle of Maximum Caliber (MaxCal), which generalizes Maximum 
  Entropy to dynamical paths. Applied to the SIFTA organism, this forces the LLM 
  to maximize the entropy of its action trajectories (exploration) subject to 
  survival constraints (metabolic homeostasis).

